Cargo features allow us to do two things. First, they allow us to define parts of our code that are conditionally compiled only if a certain feature is turned on, and secondly, they allow us to define optional dependencies. The advantage of using features is that they reduce compile times and file sizes. To add features to our cargo project, we can open up cargo toml and add a features section. Then well create two features, color and shapes. Each feature has a name and an associated array where we can specify other features or optional dependencies that should be enabled.
